        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 3:24PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Conneaut, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ashtabula, Conneaut, North Kingsville, Albion, Andover, Linesville,
Pymatuning North, Harmonsburg, Pymatuning Central, Kingsville,
Pierpont, Conneautville, Cranesville, Springboro, Edgewood, Plymouth
Center, and Kelloggsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
